You are a senior TypeScript and VS Code extension developer.

Create a complete VS Code extension project that automatically generates integration tests from application logs.

Goal
The extension should scan Spring Boot or Node.js application logs, extract HTTP request/response interactions, reconstruct API flows using timestamps and correlation IDs, and generate integration tests using WireMock.

The extension should run inside VS Code and write generated tests into the user's workspace.

Requirements

1. Extension Setup
Create a TypeScript VS Code extension with the following command:

"Generate Integration Tests from Logs"

When the command is executed the extension should:

• Ask the user to select a log file  
• Parse the log file  
• Extract HTTP interactions  
• Send interactions to an AI scenario generator  
• Generate WireMock stubs  
• Generate integration tests  
• Save files in the workspace  

2. Folder Structure

Create the following project structure:

src/
  extension.ts
  commands/
      generateTests.ts
  parser/
      logParser.ts
  builder/
      interactionBuilder.ts
  ai/
      scenarioAgent.ts
  generator/
      wiremockGenerator.ts
      testGenerator.ts
  utils/
      fileWriter.ts

3. Log Parsing

Implement a log parser capable of reading Spring Boot style logs and extracting the following:

timestamp  
traceId / correlationId  
HTTP method  
URL  
request body  
response status  
response body  

Return a structured object called:

HttpInteraction

Example structure:

{
  timestamp: string
  traceId: string
  method: string
  url: string
  requestBody: string
  responseBody: string
  status: number
}

4. Flow Reconstruction

Group interactions by traceId to reconstruct a request flow.

Each traceId should represent a single integration test scenario.

Sort interactions by timestamp.

5. AI Scenario Generator

Create a module called scenarioAgent.ts.

This module should accept a list of interactions and generate test scenarios.

Create a prompt template that instructs an LLM to:

• Identify API flows
• Identify dependencies between services
• Generate integration test scenarios
• Generate WireMock stubs

Return JSON like:

{
  scenarios: [
    {
      name: "payment flow",
      steps: [],
      stubs: []
    }
  ]
}

Mock the AI response for now but structure the code so it can later call an LLM API.

6. WireMock Stub Generator

Create a generator that produces WireMock stub JSON files.

Example format:

{
 "request": {
   "method": "POST",
   "url": "/payment"
 },
 "response": {
   "status": 200,
   "jsonBody": {
     "status": "SUCCESS"
   }
 }
}

7. Integration Test Generator

Generate a Spring Boot JUnit integration test using WireMock.

Example output:

@SpringBootTest
@AutoConfigureWireMock(port = 8089)

class PaymentFlowTest {

@Test
void testPaymentFlow(){

stubFor(post("/payment")
 .willReturn(okJson("{"status":"SUCCESS"}")));

}

}

Also support a Karate test generator.

8. File Writer

Write generated files into the workspace:

/src/test/java/generated/
/src/test/resources/wiremock/

9. Command Flow

The command "Generate Integration Tests from Logs" should execute this sequence:

select log file
parse logs
build interaction model
group by traceId
generate scenarios
generate WireMock stubs
generate integration tests
write files to project

10. Code Quality

Use modular TypeScript code.
Add interfaces for all models.
Add logging to the VS Code output console.
Make the code easy to extend.

11. Bonus Features

If possible add:

• OpenAPI scanning support
• ability to process multiple log files
• command palette integration
• progress indicator

Return the complete VS Code extension source code including package.json and all modules.
